First Lady Michelle Obama will be traveling to the United Kingdom, Italy, and Vicenza from June 15-21, 2015. In London, she will participate in events for the Let Girls Learn initiative, discussing how the UK and US are working together to expand access to girls' education worldwide. In Milan, she will lead the Presidential Delegation to the World's Fair and promote the Let's Move! initiative for a healthier nation. In Vicenza, she will visit US military service members and their families as part of the Joining Forces initiative. She will also visit cultural sites in Venice before returning to Washington, DC.